  "prompt": "How do I take admission in JNU?",
  "response": "To take admission in Jawaharlal Nehru University (JNU), you typically have to follow these steps:\n\n1. **Check Eligibility:** Research the specific eligibility criteria for the program you are interested in, as these can vary between undergraduate, postgraduate, and doctoral programs.\n\n2. **Entrance Exam:** Most programs at JNU require you to take an entrance exam. The entrance exams are usually conducted by the university itself. Check the official JNU website to find information about the specific entrance tests relevant to your intended course, such as the JNUEE (Jawaharlal Nehru University Entrance Examination).\n\n3. **Application Form:** Fill out the application form online through the JNU website. Make sure to submit all required documents, such as educational qualifications, identification proof, and any other necessary materials.\n\n4. **Payment of Fees:** Pay the necessary application fee as specified in the admission guidelines.\n\n5. **Admit Card:** After successful submission, you will receive an admit card for the entrance examination, which you must download and bring on the day of the exam.\n\n6. **Entrance Exam Preparation:** Prepare for the entrance examination according to the syllabus and structure provided by the university.\n\n7. **Results:** After the examination, results will be published on the JNU website. If you qualify, you will be called for the next stages, which may include interviews or counseling sessions.\n\n8. **Final Admission:** Successful candidates will need to complete the admission process, which includes document verification and payment of fees for the course.\n\n9. **Registration:** Once admitted, complete your registration and other formalities to join the university.\n\nAlways refer to the official JNU website or contact the admissions office for the most accurate and up-to-date information. Make sure to follow any specific instructions provided for the year you are applying, as admission procedures can change.",
